## Objective

From PLAN Section 8.8:
> **Oracle**: Metamorphic tests: indexing in "batch" vs "stream" mode yields identical search results.

## Important: Relaxed Equivalence

Unlike other optimizations, streaming indexing has **set equality**, not sequence equality:

```
∀ query: set(search_batch(query).hits.message_id) ≡ set(search_streaming(query).hits.message_id)
```

This means:
- Same results are returned
- Order may differ for tied scores
- Message IDs may differ (auto-increment timing)

## Test Strategy

### 1. Set Equality Test
```rust
#[test]
fn streaming_same_result_set() {
    let corpus = create_test_corpus();

    // Index in batch mode (default)
    let index_batch = index_batch_mode(&corpus);
    let results_batch = search(&index_batch, "test query");

    // Index in streaming mode
    env::set_var("CASS_STREAMING_INDEX", "1");
    let index_stream = index_streaming_mode(&corpus);
    let results_stream = search(&index_stream, "test query");
    env::remove_var("CASS_STREAMING_INDEX");

    // Same result SET (not necessarily order)
    let ids_batch: HashSet<_> = results_batch.iter()
        .map(|r| (r.conversation_id, r.message_idx))
        .collect();
    let ids_stream: HashSet<_> = results_stream.iter()
        .map(|r| (r.conversation_id, r.message_idx))
        .collect();

    assert_eq!(ids_batch, ids_stream, "Different result sets");
}
```

### 2. Completeness Test
```rust
